        <headline>Red Flag Warning issued April 18 at 3:34AM CDT until April 18 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a Red Flag
Warning for strong winds and low relative humidity, which is in
effect from 1 PM this afternoon to 7 PM CDT this evening.

* Affected Area...In Texas...Oldham and Deaf Smith.

* 20 Foot Winds...Southwest 20.0 to 25.0 mph with gusts up to
40.0 mph.

* Relative Humidity...As low as 10 percent.

* Red Flag Threat Index...3 to 6.

* Timing...From 1 PM to 7 PM.
</description>
        <instruction>A Red Flag Warning means that critical fire weather conditions
are either occurring now...or will shortly. A combination of
strong winds...low relative humidity...and warm temperatures will
create favorable weather for rapid fire growth and spread. Avoid
activities that promote open flames and sparks.</instruction>
